    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1905-07-04T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1905-07-04T00:00:00-05:00" n="258"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d258">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Chargé <persName type="from">Snyder</persName> to the <gloss
                            type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Bogotá</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1905-07-04">
                            <hi rend="italic">July 4, 1905</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 62.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: Referring to my No. 61 of June 29, 1905, I have
                    the honor to send you herewith copy and translation of a note received from the
                    minister for foreign affairs in answer to my note of June 29, 1905.</p>
                <p>I am, sir, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Alban G. Snyder.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
                <pb facs="0367" n="247" xml:id="pg_247"/>
                <frus:attachment>
                    <opener>
                        <seg rendition="#center">[Inclosure.—Translation.]</seg>
                    </opener>
                    <head>
                        <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Minister for Foreign
                                Affairs</gloss> to Chargé <persName type="to"
                            >Snyder</persName>.</hi>
                    </head>
                    <opener>
                        <dateline rendition="#right">
                            <placeName>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Republic of Colombia,<lb/>Ministry for Foreign
                                    Affairs</hi>,<lb/>
                                <hi rend="italic">Bogotá</hi>
                            </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1905-06-30">
                                <hi rend="italic">June 30, 1905</hi>
                            </date>.</dateline>
                    </opener>
                    <p>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: In your note of the 29th of this month your
                        honor has seen fit to transmit to me a telegram from the alcalde of Segovia,
                        Department of Antioquia, informing you that Joseff Otto, citizen of the
                        United States, was murdered on the 11th of said month.</p>
                    <p>By telegram of this date the government of Antioquia has been ordered to take
                        summary measures, if they have not already been taken, against those
                        responsible for the crime, and that the necessary measures be taken in
                        accordance with the law and consular convention between this Republic and
                        the United States, to place in security the effects left by the deceased;
                        and that information be given to this office of all the circumstances of the
                        case in order that they may be forwarded to your honor.</p>
                    <p>I improve, etc.,</p>
                    <closer>
                        <signed>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Clímaco Calderón.</hi>
                        </signed>
                    </closer>
                </frus:attachment>
            </div>
        </body>
